# Select dropdown styling

All `<select>` elements get their look from the global `select` rule in `src/style.css`. That rule sets `appearance: none`, replaces the native arrow with an SVG chevron via `background: ... no-repeat right 8px center`, and reserves `padding-right: 26px` so text never overlaps the arrow.

When adding a new dropdown:

- Do NOT redeclare `appearance`, `background`, or the padding shorthand in component-scoped styles. Overriding `background` removes the chevron; overriding the `padding` shorthand (e.g. `padding: 7px 9px`) shrinks the right padding and pushes the arrow out of position (arrow appears too far left / overlapped).
- Component styles should only adjust layout: width, flex, `min-width`, `padding-top`/`padding-bottom`, `font-size`.

```css
/* ❌ BAD — kills the chevron and misplaces the arrow */
.my-panel select {
  background: #131722;
  padding: 7px 9px;
}

/* ✅ GOOD — layout tweaks only, chevron comes from global rule */
.my-panel select {
  flex: 1;
  min-width: 0;
  padding-top: 7px;
  padding-bottom: 7px;
}
```
